flowRoot.flowPara: Selecting Emoji slides the sidebar to the right to reveal subcategories
When the Emoji section is open, a back button replaces the search button (typing still triggers search though).
Selecting Emoji slides the sidebar to the right to reveal subcategories
When the Emoji section is open, a back button replaces the search button (typing still triggers search though).
Selecting letters & symbols slides the sidebar to the right to reveal subcategories.
When the letters and symbols section is open, a back button replaces the search button (typing still triggers search though).
Recent is divided into two sections - emoji first, then letters and symbols.
Recently used only shows items from the emoji section.
Recently used only shows items from the characters section.
When search is activated, the search bar slides down but the selected section remains visible.
When text has been entered in the search box, the sidebar hides and the view selector becomes deselected. Search results are displayed below.
Cancelling search restores the previous view. Selecting a view from the view selector cancels search.
Search results are global - they include both emoji and characters.
